17/02/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The head of NATO's Advisory Team to Macedonia, Brigadier General Dennis Bliss, reiterated the importance of judicial and economic reforms for efforts to join the Pact.
Addressing a roundtable discussion on the issue Wednesday (16 February), the British general said NATO would closely follow the work of the Macedonian courts.
According to the latest opinion polls, public trust is extremely low in the courts, compared to other institutions.
In other news, Macedonian Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski met with EU Enlargement Commissioner Olli Rehn in Brussels Wednesday.
Rehn said the Union views the 13 March local elections and the start of the decentralisation process as major tests for the Macedonian government.
The same day, Macedonian President Branko Crvenkovski wrapped up a visit to Slovenia and headed on to Bosnia and Herzegovina, where he meets Thursday with members of the tripartite presidency and other officials.
(Utrinski Vesnik, Dnevnik, Vest - 17/02/05;
A1 TV, PBS BiH - 16/02/05)
